      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "name": "Black pepper",
      "amount": "to taste",
      "notes": ""
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the char-grilled yang and cook for 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "Add the minced garlic and grated ginger, and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add the minari and cook for 3-4 minutes, or until it starts to soften.",
    "Add the soy sauce and stir to coat the minari, then cook for another 2 minutes.",
    "Season with salt and black pepper to taste, then serve immediately.",
    "Garnish with additional garlic and ginger, if desired."
  ],
